      <hedline>
        <hl1>Raising the Tax On Cigarettes</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Alliance for Smoke-Free Air president Claire Millman letter on April 15 editorial supports initiative by Nassau County Executive Tom Suozzi to raise tax on cigarettes in effort to improve air quality</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thank you for your editorial ''A Tax to Clear the Air'' (April 15), in support of the laudable initiative by Thomas Suozzi, the Nassau executive, to effectively combat a major killer in our midst: tobacco smoking.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thank you for your editorial ''A Tax to Clear the Air'' (April 15), in support of the laudable initiative by Thomas Suozzi, the Nassau executive, to effectively combat a major killer in our midst: tobacco smoking.</p>
        <p>Active smoking is the No. 1 cause of preventable death in our country. Secondhand smoke, containing over 50 carcinogens, is a major cause of disease and death in nonsmokers. Increasing cigarette taxes has proved to be an effective measure in encouraging smokers to quit and deterring the youth from starting.</p>
        <p>Those smokers who argue that increased cigarette taxes are ''unfair'' should be apprised of the facts. Tobacco smoking costs our nation $167 billion every year in health care costs and lost productivity, a toll borne by all of us, in addition to the toll on our health.</p>
        <p>Claire Millman  Plainview</p>
        <p>The writer is president, Alliance for Smoke-Free Air.</p>
      </block>
